title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1984-04-27
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transfer by Andrew F. 07/2013
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Dire Wolf, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues-> The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> High Time-> Women Are Smarter-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text:
Just wrote same thing on Deadnet We would follow these guys around for a night like this. Any time they opened the set with Playin in the band it left things wide open for exploring. When one looks at this set list its apparent the band was exploring , Playin, China Doll, High Time, says it all. Given the fact that this is 29 years later and many of us still gravitate to the band is how powerful an impact they had on us then and now.
 5 stars because of the sound and set list

Mr.wonderfuli I remember both.of these shows like yesterday!providence is a beaUtiful,yet small venue!!!! For those of you who never been    There, it has beautiful Red Oriental Carpet, and tremendous sound!!!! I've seen the GD there 6 times, all were beyond Gorgeous!!!! TheBoys were Smokin tonight!  The whole show kicked butt, but They took it to the outer limits in the 2nd set!!!!! I happened to have gotten my hands on some really fun vitamin A before showtime, making it all the more incredible....this night you could listen overandover, and still love it the same!!!!  TO ALL, ENJOY THIS A++ SHOW!!!!
